                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/29/2003&nbsp;: 7:59:11 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Rekcim,<br /><br />I don't really want to come down on you, but I don't think I can help it here.<br /><br />You are viewing things from a narrow perspective, this is why you do not understand.  If you had access to all the high end loots in the game you might understand why the people killing the mobs that drop that loot are not all gung ho about ceramic crap items.<br /><br />A statless ceramic item is not going to help me channel a spell through a quad-800 hitting exp mob.  I don't care how fast it can make me cast, or how much mana it can save me.  There are limits to how much these can help you, in other words you can only cast so fast no matter what your focus is.<br /><br />I have a Staff of Lost Rituals for a very very long time now.  The only DoT that I use regularly that the focus has any noticeable effect on is Embracing Darkness.  Someone tried to make a point earlier about how longer snare means you do not have to FD as much, that is total crap and that person is a moron for stating that.  As soon as I can get a really nice upgrade for my Staff, I will.  And I couldnt care less about the focus.<br /><br />I think you are, at heart, envious of the higher end players and the 150hp items they can get and that you cannot.  Anyone with half a brain can see that more HP = more survivability.  Also, 99% of these high HP items are also heavy on the mana, and yes having 5k + manapool does make the difference.<br /><br />I wont argue against mana preservation, I think it is the best focus all around for any caster.  However, AE4 is not the end all be all.  Firstly,  MP4 and AE4 items have poor stats overall.  They are crafted or drop off lower end mobs and thusly have low end stats (excepting the elemental crafted items, which are pretty decent).  Personally, I use Miragul's arms ( 15% mp ) and I never ever come close to OOM exping (not that I exp anymore).  I can pump mana using Sedulous and Covetous chaining and not go OOM for several minutes.<br /><br />The biggest problem with AE items is that they only focus DoTs and we are so much more than just DoTs in the high end game.  As a necromancer you are much better off with a general Mana Preservation item over a specific type like AE.<br /><br />EDIT: I also want to add that I feel it is absolutely absurd that you would assume that someone such as myself, who has dedicated years to bettering his character and being the best necromancer one can possibly be, would just overlook an item that might better me in some way just because I do not like the amount of HP it gives me.  Totally absurd and ignorant.<br /><br />Vtyn<br />Arch Lich<br />Heaven and Earth</span></font></td>
